The paper deals with face recognition, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves using a generative adversarial network (GAN) to synthesize data, which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of a loss function and a two-player minimax optimization, which are common concepts in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The evaluation of the proposed method is done on a benchmark dataset, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper mentions the improvement in face recognition performance, which is a common goal in neural networks (cs.NE).
